    "Container Desktop" : {

    },
    "Container Desktop can notify you when a container exits unexpectedly or when the system stops. Turn these on or off in Settings → Notifications." : {

    },
    "Container Desktop Help" : {

    },
    "Container Desktop is a native macOS interface for Apple’s container runtime. It manages containers, images, networks, volumes, and virtual machines by driving the container command-line tool, so anything you do here matches what the tool does in Terminal." : {

    },
    "Container Desktop is up to date." : {

    },
    "Container Desktop’s version tracks the container runtime release it’s built for. System → Software Update shows the latest release from Apple and installs verified updates after an administrator prompt — Container Desktop only accepts packages signed and notarized by Apple." : {

